  <tr align="left">
    <td  bgcolor="#FFFFFF" valign="TOP"><table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" border="0">
      <tr align="left">
        <td  bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="100%" valign="top"><font color="#08599C">
         <b>Author:&nbsp;Webmaster (webby) </b><br>
         <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
           <tr>
             <td><font color="#08599C"><b>Date:&nbsp;</b></font></td>
             <td><DIV DIR="ltr"><font color="#08599C"><b>22-10-2005 15:03</b></font></DIV></td>
           </tr>
         </table>
         <br>
      Wow I have 24 hours away from here and I come back to all this doom & gloom!<br />
First of all - as per the news on the home page - Marat is going to Paris as he has commitments with Adidas and he wants to practice.<br />
Now as I have also reported Peter is with him - if Marat had no intention of practising - why would Peter go to Russia to be with him? Think they are going to sit and have a nice little chat over a cup of tea???<br />
Then all this nonsense about Marat having serious stomach problems and losing weight? Well haven't we all have had a slight problem at some stage - in fact with the serious climatic changes in the world there are lots of viruses around. Just because he is Marat doesn't mean he is immune to all the same things we suffer from.<br />
Personally I have been very impressed how fit Marat is looking. Previously when Marat has had injuries he has come back quite "chubby" as he has not kept up his gym work and kept to his proper diet. To me the fact that he looks trim and slim means that he is taking this all very seriously and is determined to at least be fit and ready to get back on court. As he has repeatedly said " I go to the doctor every morning at 8am" - Marat the one who loves to sleep until late! So does all this mean he doesn't take his injury seriously?<br />
Yes he has been seen at various events - but as he normally doesn't have time to do these things - just the fact that he has an injury does that mean he has to act like a monk and stay at home and do nothing? He is a normal fun loving young man - please give him some free time in his life to enjoy the usual things that we all seem to take for granted. Or do you all think he should have no fun at all - just practice and practice and live tennis every minute of the day?<br />
Then Shanghai - as has been said Roger is injured and will go to Shanghai without any match practice - same goes for Hewitt and now Marat. Does the fact that they are injured mean they forget how to play tennis? Nadal is carrying an injury but whatever happens they will all do their best. Marat is proud to be already accepted for Shanghai and whatever happens he will be there. Ideally he would like to play Bercy and that will still be his intention but we have to take each week as it comes.<br />
And to the fan who thinks I have nothing else to do but phone Marat every hour to find out what he is doing just to satisfy her - apart from the fact that it would be very impolite of me - I do not think it is any of our business what he is doing every minute of the day.<br />
In fact if the same fan read through all the "knee saga" reports, she would find what his daily routine consists of.<br />
So once you have all read this I trust you will try to look at the positives. It was really good to see the intelligent discussions that had been happening and I trust that we can continue in the same manner until we have some more positive news.<br />
Thank you for all being Marat's fans.<br />
webby<br />
<br />
<br />
